About 6 months ago in January, I was on a flight from Seoul to Boston, heading to the 100th Annual Meeting of the American Meteorological Society to present my research (I know I’m not very cool). I was jet lagged, alone, confused, and scarred, afraid that I didn’t measure up to the other brilliant scientific researchers. In the cold Boston wind, and again... this is Boston in January, I stumbled across Cinema Paradiso. The 3rd video is exactly how I felt balancing the 2 sides of me, the academic and the inner regular emotional self. I’m not a guy you expect to like figure skating, but I like how it gives a visual representation of how we process emotions through music. Performances like these give meaning and validation to our thoughts and emotions. Great job guys.
